# Chip

A IDS chip is a compact visual label that gives visual context to content that has been filtered or is filterable..

This is used primarily in our other IDS components, such as `DataGrid`, and `Table`.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/chip
```

```tsx
import { Chip } from '@ids-ts/chip';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `header` | `string` | No | The value for the component to display |
| `selectionLabels` | `string[]` | Yes | - |
| `dismissButtonAriaLabel` | `string` | No | - |
| `onClose` | `React.MouseEventHandler` | No | - |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface ChipProps extends ThemeableElement<'div'> {
  /** The value for the component to display */
  header?: string;
  /**
   * Selected labels that can be added for a header
   *
   */
  selectionLabels: string[];
  /**
   * Aria label for the close button
   *
   */
  dismissButtonAriaLabel?: string;
  /**
   * Callback when component is closed.
   *
   */
  onClose?: React.MouseEventHandler;
}
```

</details>

